&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About SurePay&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2016, SurePay is the leading account verification platform, relied upon by 250+ banks and thousands of organizations, to prevent fraud, misdirected payments, and reputational damage. Headquartered in Utrecht, we are scaling our platform and our team across Europe and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our core Account Verification product has already changed the game. Now, we are scaling our vision. We’ve launched a new domain—Focussed on Fraud &amp;amp; AML prevention and detection—to build a powerhouse suite of actionable insights for Fraud and Anti-Money Laundering. The train has already left the station: we have a vision, a working prototype, and positive validation from major banks. To maintain this momentum, we are adding a second Product Manager to our team. Your goal is to transform early-stage prototypes into high-value, market-ready products by the end of 2026. You will solve a critical problem for banks: the increasing complexity of financial crime. By translating market needs into a technical roadmap, you ensure SurePay remains the primary defense layer for our customers. This role is directly tied to our company’s objective of diversifying our revenue streams beyond core products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product Execution: Co-manage the lifecycle from concept to &quot;Go-Live&quot;. You ensure we don&#39;t just build features, but solutions that work in a production environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer &amp;amp; Market Intelligence: Engage directly with banks to distill their &quot;pain&quot; into requirements. You’ll perform competitive analysis to ensure we stay two steps ahead.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Roadmap &amp;amp; Requirements: Define prioritized features and build the business cases behind them. You’ll translate &quot;we need to stop fraud&quot; into specific, actionable API and data requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Beta/Pilot Management: Oversee the &quot;messy&quot; phase of testing. You’ll run pilot programs, collect raw feedback, and iterate quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal Leadership: Act as the bridge between Business Development, Product Owners, and Customer Success to ensure our internal teams are as excited and informed as our customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a pragmatic, knowledgeable Product Manager who understands the European banking landscape and isn&#39;t intimidated by the ambiguity of a scale-up environment. You have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years in Product Management (EU market), specifically within SaaS or API-based products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Domain Expertise: A solid background in Fraud Prevention, AML, or Payments. You should&amp;nbsp; have an understanding of how banks monitor transactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Savvy: You are comfortable using both qualitative research and quantitative data to back up your roadmap decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Straightforward communication skills: You present ideas clearly and give/receive feedback without fluff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pragmatic &amp;amp; Agile: You are not rattled by the &quot;messiness&quot; of a scale-up and comfortable with ambiguity. Collaboration skills: You thrive in a team setting but take individual ownership of your product’s success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary + 8% personal benefits budget (use it on training, more time off, or your salary)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25 holidays&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid working setup (1 day per week in Utrecht)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MacBook Pro, iPhone, and all the tech you need&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel costs covered (NS Business Card)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pension plan&lt;/li&gt;
